    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-22T15:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-22T15:55:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Elsey Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Thomas</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-22T16:55:00-04:00"
                            >February 22, 1948—4:55 p. m. EST.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Blue1">Blue</gloss> 4. Your working draft of recommended basic
                        position<note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">See <ref target="#pg_637">p.
                        637</ref>.</note> for Security Council discussion Tuesday received. I
                    approve in principle this basic position. I want to make it clear, however, that
                    nothing should be presented to Security Council that could be interpreted as a
                    recession on our part from the position we took in the General Assembly.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">On November 29, 1947, i.e., in support of the
                        partition of Palestine into Jewish and Arab states.</note> Send final draft
                    of Austin’s remarks for my consideration.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
